# BuildSaudi Cursor Rules

## Pre-Deploy Testing (MANDATORY)
Before pushing ANY code change to production:
1. Run `npm run build` to catch TypeScript and build errors
2. Run `npm run dev` and manually verify the change works on both desktop AND mobile viewports
3. If the change involves UI, check it at 375px (mobile) and 1440px (desktop) widths
4. Only push to `main` after confirming the build succeeds and the feature works as expected
5. Never push broken or untested code — `main` auto-deploys to production via Vercel
